      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon tests or certified material datasheets; geometric inputs from CMM measurements. Required Gradation 3: input uncertainty characterized with distributions.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength distributions derived from lot-specific tensile coupon tests (n=5 per lot). Geometric dimensions from CMM measurements with 0.01 mm resolution. Input distributions propagated through the UQ campaign (Monte Carlo, n=1000) documented in TR-2023-NC-01; Sobol indices confirm cortical modulus dominance."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection of test articles documented. Required Gradation 3: statistical characterization of sample population.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs drawn from two production lots tested across two independent laboratories. All constructs dimensionally inspected by CMM; mean and standard deviation of critical dimensions reported. Sample population adequately characterizes manufacturing variability."
