      "rationale": "Stiffness governs load sharing with bone graft; yield force bounds the onset of permanent deformation that may compromise fixation; force at 40 mm displacement represents a surrogate for clinical failure load. All three QoIs are directly cited in the 510(k) predicate comparison and are relevant to the COU."
